        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Some related Strombidium species, arrows mark the anterior end of the ventral kinety. (A) Strombidium acutum (from Lynn et al. 1988); (B) S. basimorphum (from Martin and Montagnes 1993); (C) S. dalum (from Lynn et al. 1988); (D) S. crassulum (from Leegaard 1915); (E) S. epidemum (from Lynn et al. 1988); (F) S. inclinatum (from Montagnes et al. 1990); (G) S. compressum (from Lynn et al. 1988); (H) S. sulcatum (from Song et al. 2000); (I) S. taylori (from Martin and Montagnes 1993); (J) S. emergens (from Lynn et al. 1988); (K) S. rhynchum (from Lynn et al. 1988); (L) S. tressum (from Lynn et al. 1988); (M) S. υentropinnum (from Martin and Montagnes 1993); (N) S. petzi (from Petz et al. 1995); (O, P) S. crassulum (from Petz et al. 1995). Scale bars: 20 mm (A, D, G, H, J, K, M, N); 30 mm (B); 15 mm (C, E, F, I, L); 40 mm (O, P)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4581302/files/figure.png" .

